(14, 'INTRODUCTION', '<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. It&nbsp;is the language for describing the presentation of Web pages, including colours, layout, and fonts, thus making our web pages presentable to the users.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">CSS is designed to make style sheets for the web. It is independent of HTML and can be used with any XML-based markup language. Now let&rsquo;s try to break the acronym:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Cascading: Falling of Styles</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Style: Adding designs/Styling our HTML tags</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sheets: Writing our style in different documents</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>&nbsp;CSS History</strong></u></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">1994: First Proposed by Hakon Wium Lie on 10th October</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">1996: CSS was published on 17th November with influencer Bert Bos</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Later he became co-author of CSS</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">1996: CSS became official with CSS was published in December</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">1997: Created CSS level 2 on 4th November&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">1998: Published on 12th May</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>&nbsp;CSS Editors</strong></u></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Some of the popular editors that are best suited to wire CSS code are as following:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Atom</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Visual Studio Code</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Brackets</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Espresso(For Mac OS&nbsp; User)</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Notepad++(Great for HTML &amp; CSS)</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Komodo Edit (Simple)</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Sublime Text (Best Editor)</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>&nbsp;<u>CSS Syntax</u></strong></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>Selector { Property 1 : value; Property 2 : value; Property 3 : value; } For example: h1 { Color: red; Text-align: center; } #unique { color: green; } </code></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Selector: selects the element you want to target</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Always remains the same whether we apply internal or external styling&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">There are few basic selectors like tags, id&rsquo;s, and classes</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">All forms this key-value pair</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Keys: properties(attributes) like color, font-size, background, width, height,etc</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Value: values associated with these properties.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>CSS Comment</strong></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Comments don&rsquo;t render on the browser</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Helps to understand our code better and makes it readable.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Helps to debug our code</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Two ways to&nbsp; comment:</span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Single line&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code> /*&lt;h6&gt; This represents the most/ least important line of the doc. &lt;/h6&gt;*/</code></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Here is how to comment out multiple lines:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>\r\n /*\r\n         h1\r\n     {\r\n     color: red;\r\n     text-align: center;\r\n      } \r\n      */</code></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>&nbsp;CSS How-To&nbsp;</strong></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">There are 3 ways to write CSS in our HTML file.</span>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Inline CSS</span></li>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Internal CSS</span></li>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">External CSS</span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Priority order</span>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Inline &gt; Internal &gt; External</span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Inline CSS</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Before CSS this was the only way to apply styles</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Not an efficient way to write as it has a lot of redundancy</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Self-contained&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Uniquely applied on each element</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">The idea of separation of concerns was lost</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Example:</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>&lt;h3 style=&rdquo; color:red&rdquo;&gt; Have a great day &lt;/h3&gt;\r\n&lt;p  style =&rdquo; color: green&rdquo;&gt; I did this , I did that &lt;/p&gt;</code></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Internal CSS</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">With the help of style tag, we can apply styles within the HTML file</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">&nbsp;Redundancy is removed</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">But the idea of separation of concerns still lost</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Uniquely applied on a single document</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Example:</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>    &lt; style&gt;\r\n              h1{\r\n                     color:red;\r\n                   }\r\n     &lt;/style&gt;  \r\n    &lt;h3&gt; Have a great day &lt;/h3&gt;</code></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;External CSS</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">With the help of &lt;link&gt; tag in the head tag, we can apply styles</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Reference is added&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">File saved with .css extension</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Redundancy is removed</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">The idea of separation of concerns is maintained</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Uniquely applied to each document</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Example:</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>&lt;head&gt;\r\n &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; type=&quot;text/css&quot; href=&quot;name of the Css file&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;\r\n            h1{\r\n                     color:red;         //.css file\r\n                 }</code></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>Implementation of all the three types of CSS:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\r\n&lt;html&gt;\r\n&lt;head&gt;\r\n	&lt;title&gt;HTML&lt;/title&gt;\r\n	&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; type=&quot;text/css&quot; href=&quot;first.css&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;style&gt;\r\nh1\r\n{\r\n   color:green;\r\n} \r\n&lt;/style&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;\r\n&lt;body&gt;\r\n&lt;h1&gt;This heading will be green&lt;/h1&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color:Red&quot;&gt;This paragraph will be red&lt;/p&gt; \r\n&lt;p  id=&quot;center&quot;&gt;This paragraph will be pink and center-aligned&lt;/p&gt; \r\n&lt;/body&gt;\r\n&lt;/html&gt;\r\nThis is Css file\r\n#center {\r\n  text-align: center;\r\n  color:pink;\r\n}</code></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>CSS Selectors</strong></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">The selector is used to target elements and apply CSS&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Three simple selectors</span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Element Selector&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Id Selector</span></li>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Class Selector</span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Priority of Selectors</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Id &gt; Class&gt;Element</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Element Selector</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Used to select HTML elements by its name</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">How we do it</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>h1\r\n     {\r\n      Color: red;\r\n     }</code></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">We selected the heading tag and then changed the color property i.e text color to red. Now whatever is written in this tag (content) will have the text color as red&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;ID Selector</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">The id attribute is used to select HTML element</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Used to target specific or unique element&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">How we do it</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>#unique\r\n     {\r\n      Color: red;\r\n     }\r\n&lt;h1 id=&rdquo;unique&rdquo;&gt; Hi &lt;/p&gt;</code></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">We selected the id and then changed the color property i.e text color to red. Now whatever is written in this tag (content) will have the text color as red&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Class Selector</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">The class attribute is used to select HTML element</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Used to target a specific class of the element&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\">How we do it</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>group\r\n     {\r\n      Color: red;\r\n     }\r\n&lt;h1 class=&rdquo;group&rdquo;&gt; Hi &lt;/p&gt;</code></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">We selected the class and then changed the color property i.e text color to red. Now whatever is written in this tag (content) will have the text color as red&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>Implementation of all the three selectors in CSS:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\r\n&lt;html&gt;\r\n&lt;head&gt;\r\n	&lt;title&gt;HTML&lt;/title&gt;\r\n	&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; type=&quot;text/css&quot; href=&quot;first.css&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;style&gt;\r\n\r\n#center1 {\r\n  text-align: center;\r\n  color:pink;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.center2 {\r\n  text-align: center;\r\n  color:red;\r\n}\r\n\r\nh1\r\n{\r\n  text-align:center;\r\n   color:green;\r\n} \r\n\r\n&lt;/style&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;\r\n&lt;body&gt;\r\n&lt;h1&gt;This heading will be green  and center-aligned &lt;/h1&gt;\r\n&lt;p class = &quot;center2&quot;&gt;This paragraph will be red  and center-aligned &lt;/p&gt; \r\n&lt;p  id =&quot;center1&quot;&gt;This paragraph will be pink and center-aligned&lt;/p&gt; \r\n&lt;/body&gt;\r\n&lt;/html&gt;\r\n</code></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><code>Goto the CSS module to learn in greater depth.</code></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'CSS'),
(17, 'HTML', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>Attributes</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Attributes are used to define the property of an HTML element or to customize it based on the context of its use.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">It consists of 2 parts </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:upper-roman\">\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Attributes names: It is the property that we want to set.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Attributes values: It is the value of the attribute(property)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">&nbsp; &nbsp; Ex- <em><strong>font-size:18px;</strong></em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">&nbsp; &nbsp; Here, <strong>font-size</strong> is the attribute and <strong>18px</strong> is attribute value</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">There are 2 types of attributes.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:upper-roman\">\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Global attributes: It can be used on any of the elements in HTML file.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Examples- hidden, id, lang, spellcheck, style, title, class, dir, etc</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:upper-roman\">\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Element specific attributes: It can only be some on specific elements.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-size:16px\">&nbsp;Examples-</span><span style=\"font-size:18px\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n', 'Attributes'),
(18, 'HTML', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>Hyperlinks</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Any content, text, images, or link can be linked to a new page.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The text that is used to link to other page is known as anchor text.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Ex- <strong>&lt;a&gt; click here &lt;/a&gt;</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The anchor text is enclosed within a container and we use &lsquo;href&rsquo; attribute to specific location of the page we want to link. The value of the &lsquo;href&rsquo; attribute is the URL of the page needed to link.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;a href=&rdquo;https://google.com&nbsp;&ldquo;&gt;click here &lt;/a&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;.href =&nbsp;hypertext reference.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">This will open the page we wanted to link in the same tab. In order to open the link in new tab, we use &lsquo;target&rsquo; attribute within the anchor tag.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;a href=&rdquo; copied URL &ldquo;target=&rdquo; blank&rdquo;&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Click here &lt;/a&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>Relative reference </u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;a href =&rdquo; B/C.html&rdquo;&gt;link to c.html from a1.html&lt;/a&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;a href&nbsp; =&rdquo; ../../a html&rdquo;&gt;link to a2 html from c.html&lt;/a&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Relative reference Is shorter and portable.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The 2 types of anchor tag target attributes are:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Target=&rdquo;_blanks&rdquo; </span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;a href=&rdquo;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India</a>&rdquo; target=&rdquo;_blank&rdquo;&gt;This will open in another tab&lt;/a&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Target=&rdquo; self&rdquo;</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">If no target is used, default value is _self.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;a href=&rdquo; https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India&rdquo;&nbsp; target=&rdquo;_self&rdquo;&gt; This will open in same tab&lt;/a&gt;.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">HTML pages are used to define structure of the page and to add text contents, media, links etc. usually they do not have any style elements mentioned in it. In this case, index.html is an html is an html page and we will use that page to define structure of a web page.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Hyperlinks'),
(19, 'HTML', '<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">While most HTML tags are used to create elements, HTML also provides in-text formatting tags to apply specific<br />\r\ntext-related styles to portions of text. This topic includes examples of HTML text formatting such as highlighting,<br />\r\nbolding, underlining, subscript, and stricken text.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Highlighting</strong></u><br />\r\nThe &lt;mark&gt;&nbsp;element is new in HTML5 and is used to mark or highlight text in a document &quot;due to its relevance in<br />\r\nanother context&quot;<br />\r\nThe most common example would be in the results of a search were the user has entered a search query and<br />\r\nresults are shown highlighting the desired query.<br />\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here is some content from an article that contains the &lt;mark&gt;searched query&lt;/mark&gt;<br />\r\nthat we are looking for. Highlighting the text will make it easier for the user to<br />\r\nfind what they are looking for.&lt;/p&gt;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Bold, Italic, and Underline</strong></u><br />\r\nBold Text<br />\r\nTo bold text, use the &lt;strong&gt; or &lt;b&gt; tags:<br />\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Bold Text Here&lt;/strong&gt;<br />\r\nor<br />\r\n&lt;b&gt;Bold Text Here&lt;/b&gt;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nItalic Text<br />\r\nTo italicize text, use the &lt;em&gt; or &lt;i&gt; tags:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">&lt;em&gt;Italicized Text Here&lt;/em&gt;<br />\r\nor<br />\r\n&lt;i&gt;Italicized Text Here&lt;/i&gt;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Underlined Text<br />\r\n&lt;p&gt;This paragraph contains some &lt;u&gt;mispelled&lt;/u&gt; text.&lt;/p&gt;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>&nbsp;Abbreviation</strong></u><br />\r\nTo mark some expression as an abbreviation, use &lt;abbr&gt; tag:<br />\r\n&lt;p&gt;I like to write &lt;abbr title=&quot;Hypertext Markup Language&quot;&gt;HTML&lt;/abbr&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;<br />\r\nIf present, the title attribute is used to present the full description of such abbreviation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Inserted, Deleted, or Stricken</strong></u><br />\r\nTo mark text as inserted, use the &lt;ins&gt; tag:<br />\r\n&lt;ins&gt;New Text&lt;/ins&gt;<br />\r\nTo mark text as deleted, use the &lt;del&gt; tag:<br />\r\n&lt;del&gt;Deleted Text&lt;/del&gt;<br />\r\nTo strike through text, use the &lt;s&gt; tag:<br />\r\n&lt;s&gt;Struck-through text here&lt;/s&gt;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Superscript and Subscript</strong></u><br />\r\nTo offset text either upward or downward you can use the tags &lt;sup&gt; and &lt;sub&gt;.<br />\r\nTo create superscript:<br />\r\n&lt;sup&gt;superscript here&lt;/sup&gt;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">To create subscript:<br />\r\n&lt;sub&gt;subscript here&lt;/sub&gt;</span></p>\r\n', 'Text formatting'),
(20, 'HTML', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>BOX-MODEL</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Every HTML element can be consider as a box.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Each box has following 4 properties </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:upper-roman\">\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Content: The innermost layer. It can be anything. I. e text or images</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Padding: it clears area around content padding is always transparent. If not specified default value is zero.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Border: we can chance the color of the border, if not specified, it is transparent.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Margin: margin clears area outside the border, like padding, margin is transparent.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; *Default margin of body is 8px.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; *You can set the width of the border using border using border width property and can set the style of the border using border-style (hidden, dotted, dashed, solid,&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;double)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>&nbsp;Padding</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">These are the different ways to give the padding:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Padding sets a transparent spare on all sides of the content.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">We use padding property to specify how much padding we want to add on all the four sides of the content.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Ex- padding: 10px;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">If you want to add a padding of 10px only on the top, you can use</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Padding-top: 10px;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Padding-bottom: 5px;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Padding-left: 10px;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Padding-right: 5px;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Shorthand property:</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Padding: 10px 0px 10px 0px;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Padding; top right bottom left</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>Border</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp; Border mark the ending of the element and depends on the height and width, it is present around the padding on all the 4 slides, because of the initial default&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;value, the border is transparent.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Shorthand border property.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Border: 1px #000 solid</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Border: width style</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Like padding</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Border-right: 5px;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Border-bottom: 15px;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Border-width: 0px 5px 15px 0px;</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>Margin</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Margin clears an area around all the 4 slides of the border.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Ex- margin: n px;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Shorthand property</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Margin: 0px 25px&nbsp;&nbsp; 0px 8px;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>Color</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Text: It defined the color of the text used in the selector element.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Background: It defines the background of the text.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;Color: rgb(0,0,255) blue color</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Code: Hexadecimal numbers #0000FF blue color</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>FONTS</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">There are a number of font properties that one can apply.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Font styles</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Font variant</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Font weight normal, light, bold, inherit,</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Font size</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Line height</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Font family</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Font shorthand property: It allows us to use all font properties within single line declaration.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;..h4 {font: italic small-caps bolder 28px arial, sans-serif;}</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">HTML selector {font: style variant weight size height family}</span></span></p>\r\n', 'Box Model'),
(21, 'HTML', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>LISTS</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">There are two types:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:upper-roman\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Ordered lists</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Unordered lists</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Ordered lists</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;ol&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Contains serial numbers</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;ol&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;li&gt;------&lt;/li&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;li&gt;------&lt;/li&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;/ol&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">We can assign roman numbers using type class in opening ordered list tag.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<u><strong> Unordered lists</strong></u></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Contains bullets square, arrows</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;ul&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;li&gt;-----&lt;/li&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;li&gt;-----&lt;/li&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;/ul&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:123px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">We can change the symbols by using type class in opening unordered list tag.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>Definition list</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;dl&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;dt&gt; defining terms &lt;/dt&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;dd&gt; definition &lt;/dd&gt; &lt;br/&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;/dl&gt;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>STYLING LISTS</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Ordered list type attributes:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Type= &ldquo;a&rdquo; sets type lowercase letters</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Type= &ldquo;A&rdquo; sets uppercase letters</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Type= &rdquo;i&rdquo; sets lowercase roman numericals</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Type= &ldquo;I&rdquo; sets uppercase roman numericals</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Type = &ldquo;1&rdquo; sets numbers(default).</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Unordered lists type attributes:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Type= &ldquo;circle&rdquo; sets circular bullets</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Type= &ldquo;disc&rdquo; sets disc type bullets</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Type =&rdquo;none&rdquo; sets no bullets.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Lists'),
(22, 'HTML', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>Some Commonly used colors</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"MsoTableGrid\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">colors</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Hex value</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.3pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">RGB code(rgba)</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">white</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">#FFFFFF</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.3pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">(255, 255, 255)</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Red</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">#FF0000</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.3pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">(255, 0,0)</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Lime</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">#00FF00</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.3pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">(0, 255, 0)</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Blue</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">#0000FF</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.3pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">(0, 0, 255)</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Yellow</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">#FFFF00</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.3pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">(0, 255, 255)</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Gray</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">#808080</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.3pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">(128,128,128)</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">purple</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Green</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Silver</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.25pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">#800080</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">#008000</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">#C0C0C0</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.3pt\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">(128,0,128)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">(0,128,0)</span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">(192,192,192)</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>Priority in editor:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Color names &lt; rgbx = Hex value</span></span></p>\r\n', 'Color Codes'),
(23, 'CSS', '<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp; A button should have some background-color, border-radius, some padding and different text-color.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;style&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Button {</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Color:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Background-color:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Padding:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Text-decoration:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Border-radius:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">}</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;style&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;a href =&rdquo; link&rdquo; class=&rdquo; button&rdquo;, target=&rdquo;&gt; button name&lt;/a&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n', 'Styling a Button'),
(24, 'CSS', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><u>Priority level for styling</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">If you want to define internal styling to yours HTML page, write the style statements inside the style element and the style element and place it below the link to the external CSS file.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;head&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;link&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rel=&rdquo; stylesheet&rdquo;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Type=&rdquo; text/CSS&rdquo;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Href=&rdquo; style.CSS&rdquo;&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;style&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Internal style</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&lt;/head&gt;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; This is the ideal way to link external CSS first and then internal CSS.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;If external CSS is added before external CSS. Then external CSS will have higher priority than internal CSS.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The inline CSS is always executed first in all cases.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Inline&gt;internal&gt;External</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Priority level for styling');
